UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.description: Ninilchik to Wasilla: Michael Portillo begins a journey across Alaska, learning its links with Russia, feeding a sea otter pup and joining the US Arctic Warriors for parachute training. S4 Ep1

UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.title: Great American Railroad Journeys
UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.description: Talkeetna to Juneau: Michael Portillo continues to explore Alaska, helping a homesteader fell a tree to clear land for a log cabin and meeting scientists studying the Northern Lights. S4 Ep2

UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.title: Bangers & Cash
UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.description: Bedford Caravanette/MGC: An impressive collection of five iconic cars arrives at Thornton le Dale, including a 1967 Crayford Corsair and a 1966 Ford Zodiac which emerge from a garage in Selby. S4 Ep3

UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.title: Bangers & Cash
UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.description: Cortina 2000E/Daimler V250: Nothing screams 1970s more than a Mk3 Ford Cortina 2000E. Derek Mathewson heads to Brigg to value a 1974 example with classic Coke bottle styling and a Pinto engine. S4 Ep4

UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.title: Adolf Hitler's War

UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.title: The World at War
UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.description: On Our Way: Recalling America's entry into World War II after the Japanese attack on Pearl Harbor, the great Laurence Olivier sheds more light on the deadliest conflict in history. S1 Ep7

UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.description: Bath 2: Fiona Bruce and the team of valuers welcome visitors to the Assembly Rooms, Bath. S32 Ep18

UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.description: Ironbridge: Fiona Bruce presents from Blists Hill Victorian Town near Ironbridge in Shropshire, where items include a set of early puppets. S32 Ep19

UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.description: Ford Escort Mexico: Derek has sold everything from trucks to bicycles - but he can't remember the last time he auctioned off a two-seater plane. S7 Ep3

UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.title: Bangers & Cash
UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.description: Sunbeam Rapier: 100 motorbikes come in for auction from every era of the 20th century. Also, the team assess a 1965 Vanden Plas Princess with a four litre Rolls Royce engine. S7 Ep4

UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.description: Bentley S3/BSA 3-wheeler: Derek heads to Suffolk to collect two Bentleys with a majestic pedigree; Cynthia a stunning 1963 S3 and Harry, a 1965 Continental. S4 Ep6

UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.description: German Aviation: The untold secret story of war production that shaped the Second World War, beginning with how the German aviation industry came to dominate the skies of Europe. S1 Ep1

UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.description: The Desert: Laurence Olivier narrates this exhaustive account of World War II. In the deserts of North Africa, the 8th Army battles against Rommel's Afrika Korps. S1 Ep8

UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.description: Leeds 1: Fiona Bruce presents as the team values rarities at Leeds Town Hall. Among the items brought in by West Yorkshire residents are a valuable diamond brooch. S32 Ep20

UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.description: Leeds 2: Fiona Bruce presents the second programme from Leeds Town Hall. The experts value an enormous sculpture of carved elephants. S32 Ep21

UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.description: Fiat 500: A rusty 1970 Fiat 500 goes under the hammer - Derek reckons it's the kind of vehicle that is so iconic that it has to be saved. S7 Ep5

UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.title: Bangers & Cash
UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.description: Willys Jeep: Tucked away in the showroom is a WW2-era Willys Jeep. Its original condition means there might be a bunfight for a military vehicle that's ripe for restoration. S7 Ep6
